Privacy Policy for No Break Chain
Effective Date: March 13, 2026

No Break Chain (the "App") is provided as a Freemium app. This SERVICE is provided at no cost for basic features and is intended for use as is, with optional premium subscriptions available.

This page is used to inform visitors regarding our policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal Information if anyone decided to use our Service.

If you choose to use our Service, then you agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy.

Information Collection and Use
The App is designed to help you track daily habits and maintain streaks. To provide this functionality, the App stores all of your habit names, streak counts, and check-in logs locally on your device.

We value your privacy. We do not transmit, upload, or share any of your habit data, text entries, or usage history to our servers.

Health and Fitness Data Disclosure
Because No Break Chain can be used to track habits related to exercise, diet, wellness, or other physical activities, Google Play may categorize certain user inputs as "Health and Fitness Data."

Please be aware of the following regarding any health or fitness-related information you enter:

Local Storage Only: We do not collect, transmit, or share your health, fitness, or wellness data. Any habit names (e.g., "Drink Water," "Run 5km," "Take Medication") and their associated check-in logs are stored exclusively in the local SQLite database on your device.
No Third-Party Sharing: Since the data never leaves your device, we do not share your health data with third parties, advertising networks, or data brokers.
Data Control: You have full control over your data. You can delete all your habits and logs at any time by using the "Reset All Data" option in the App's Settings, or by uninstalling the application.
Log Data
We want to inform you that whenever you use our Service, in a case of an error in the app we may collect data and information (through third-party products) on your phone called Log Data. This Log Data may include information such as your device Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the app when utilizing our Service, the time and date of your use of the Service, and other statistics. This data does not include your local habit entries.

In-App Purchases (RevenueCat)
If you choose to upgrade to our Premium subscription, the transaction is processed through Google Play and managed via the RevenueCat SDK. RevenueCat may collect anonymous App User IDs and purchase history to validate your subscription status. RevenueCat does not have access to your locally stored habit names or logs.

Security
We value your trust in providing us your Personal Information (which is limited strictly to anonymous identifiers used for crash reporting or subscription validation), thus we are striving to use commercially acceptable means of protecting it. But remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security. Since your habit data is stored locally, the security of that data relies on the security of your device.

